snippet.textDisplay: Only 8 minutes into the video and I'm just like... sectioning for Bleach tends to be around 1/4 of an inch and you also want to use maybe 20 volume for the back and then 30 for the rest of the head so that way by the time you're done with the front of the head the back will be ready. Since her hair is very dark though I would honestly suggest maybe a 30 for the back and a 40 for the front. If anyone else has any kind of suggestions I would love to know. I'm actually studying to become a cosmetologist and would love to hear from other people.

snippet.textDisplay: Story time! Well before the time of Hairdresser Reacts I had 2005 emo box dye black hair. In the shift to scene season, I bought a White Out bleach kit from Hot Topic and decided I was going to bring it to blonde so I could throw some Manic Panic up in that bitch. I left it on for ??? Idk a long time. Had an identical scene to her on her hands and knees in the tub pulling out hair, except my hair was really long and thick before this happened. The entire bottom of my tub was covered in a layer of my own hair. I pulled it out in handfuls while I washed it. I made the same mistake as her continuing to brush more of it out too. I was sobbing with clumps of my own hair in hand, but what was left of my hair was blooooonde bayyybeee. My grandma took me to her hairdresser to try to recover it with a cut and deep conditioning and I went from nearly to my bum hair to barely longer than a pixie cut, and even that was still fried hair. Took over 10 years for me to start having decent growth again.
